Heat oven to 325 degrees F. Lightly spray 11x7-inch baking dish with cooking spray. Place tenderloins in baking dish, thinner portions overlapping to make an even thickness overall. Roast 45 minutes. Mix mole sauce and raisins; pour over turkey. Bake about 45 additional minutes or until center reaches 165 degrees F. on instant read thermometer; basting with sauce every 10 minutes. Slice turkey and arrange on platter. Spoon some of mole sauce over slices and remainder around edges. Sprinkle with pine nuts.